active directory certificate services (ADCS) is used for issuing and managing PKI certificates
we can use misconfigurations in ADCS to escalate priviliges and achieve persistence

enumeration using certify
    beacon> execute-assembly C:\Tools\Certify\Certify\bin\Release\Certify.exe enum-cas --quiet
    this will return information about CA and sub-CAs in the domain, along with their potential vulnerabilities

ESC1 vulnerability:
    priv esc vuln that occurs when an attacker can enroll for a cert that has an EKU that enables client authentication
    and where subject info can be supplied by the requester
    enumeration for this vuln:
        beacon> execute-assembly C:\Tools\Certify\Certify\bin\Release\Certify.exe enum-templates --filter-enabled --filter-vulnerable --hide-admins --quiet
            we're looking for the ENROLLEE_SUPPLIES_SUBJECT flag, client auth in the extended key usage